":490},"Text based on photograph",{"note":492},"Castelli, Ferrara, Franz, and Kaibel read the inscription intact",{"type":494,"xml:lang":165,"resp":439,"p":495},"translation","To the underworld deities. Merkouriales lived for 42 years. His wife made (this).",{"type":494,"xml:lang":359,"resp":422,"p":497},"Alle divinità infere. Merkouriales visse per 42 anni. Sua moglie realizzò (questo).",{"type":499,"p":500},"commentary",{"_":501,"foreign":502,"ref":509},"Kaibel believed the inscription to be urban, but according to Korhonen the structure is typical of Catania. The epitaph, in fact, presents, after the traditional invocation to the underworld deities, the name of the deceased, his age and in another sentence the dedicant and the dedication verb. The form  is also attested in IMusCatania 65 = . Moreover, Korhonen dates the ink writing ‘Catania’ below the text to the 18th century and believes it refers to the findspot. The name of the deceased, , is a translation of the Latin , but it does not seem to be other parallels in Sicily. The dedicant is anonym but the type of kinship with the deceased is expressed: the lack of the article before  is notable, but it has parallels (IGUR 958).",[503,504,505,507],{"_":472,"xml:lang":92},{"_":475,"xml:lang":92},{"_":506,"xml:lang":363},"Mercurialis",{"_":508,"xml:lang":92},"γυνή",{"_":510,"target":511},"ISic003223","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003223",{"type":513,"listBibl":514},"bibliography",[515,537],{"type":94,"bibl":516},[517,520,523,528,531,534],{"author":97,"date":98,"citedRange":99,"ptr":518,"ref":519},{"target":101},{"_":103,"target":103},{"author":105,"date":106,"citedRange":107,"ptr":521,"ref":522},{"target":109},{"_":111,"target":111},{"type":113,"n":114,"citedRange":524,"ptr":526,"ref":527},{"ref":525},{"_":117,"target":118},{"target":120},{"_":122,"target":122},{"type":113,"n":124,"citedRange":125,"ptr":529,"ref":530},{"target":127},{"_":129,"target":129},{"type":113,"n":131,"citedRange":132,"ptr":532,"ref":533},{"target":134},{"_":136,"target":136},{"type":113,"n":138,"author":139,"date":140,"citedRange":141,"ptr":535,"ref":536},{"target":143},{"_":145,"target":145},{"type":147,"bibl":41},[539],{"n":428,"url":82,"height":429,"width":430,"desc":83,"surfaceType":425},{"title":541,"body":542,"divs":543,"images":559},"ISic003246. Epitaph for Merkouriales","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003246_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003246_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003246.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003246-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΜΕΡΚΟΥΡΙΑΛΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΕΖ\u003C/span>ΗΣΕΝΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΒ´\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΓΥΝ\u003C/span>ΗΕΠΟΙΣΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Castelli, Ferrara, Franz, and Kaibel read the inscription intact\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld deities. Merkouriales lived for 42 years. His wife made (this).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Alle divinità infere. Merkouriales visse per 42 anni. Sua moglie realizzò (questo).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Kaibel believed the inscription to be urban, but according to Korhonen the structure is typical of Catania. The epitaph, in fact, presents, after the traditional invocation to the underworld deities, the name of the deceased, his age and in another sentence the dedicant and the dedication verb. The form \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔποισε\u003C/span> is also attested in IMusCatania 65 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003223\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003223\u003C/a>. Moreover, Korhonen dates the ink writing ‘Catania’ below the text to the 18th century and believes it refers to the findspot. The name of the deceased, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Μερκουριάλης\u003C/span>, is a translation of the Latin \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">Mercurialis\u003C/span>, but it does not seem to be other parallels in Sicily. The dedicant is anonym but the type of kinship with the deceased is expressed: the lack of the article before \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">γυνή\u003C/span> is notable, but it has parallels (IGUR 958).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 146 no.34 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 343 no.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.1852\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 110 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 3.5716 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Moretti 1968-1990 787 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000015\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000015\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[544,546,548,550,552,554,556],{"id":94,"html":545},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΘΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΜΕΡΚΟΥΡΙΑΛΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΕΖ\u003C/span>ΗΣΕΝΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΒ´\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΓΥΝ\u003C/span>ΗΕΠΟΙΣΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":486,"html":547},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Castelli, Ferrara, Franz, and Kaibel read the inscription intact\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":494,"html":549},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld deities. Merkouriales lived for 42 years. His wife made (this).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":494,"html":551},"\u003Ch2>Italian t